videos.description: A'ja Wilson speeds to the other side of the court to receive a pass from Tyasha Harris and Wilson scores a nice layup in transition.
videos.headline: South Carolina's Wilson races for layup

videos.description: Jazzmun Holmes goes to score but Mikiah Herbert Harrigan rises up and swats the ball away in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Harrigan stops Mississippi State bucket

videos.description: Jazzmun Holmes finds Chloe Bibby for an easy bucket to shrink Mississippi State's deficit. On the other side, Bibby makes a good defensive move and doesn't let South Carolina score.
videos.headline: Bibby shows off on both sides of the court

videos.description: Morgan William loses the ball and on the other side Doniyah Cliney hits a layup to put South Carolina back in front early in the third quarter.
videos.headline: South Carolina capitalizes on Mississippi State turnover

videos.description: Doniyah Cliney races down the court and knocks in a three-pointer at the end of the third quarter to extend South Carolina's lead to 44-39.
videos.headline: South Carolina's Cliney drills epic triple at buzzer

videos.description: Jazzmun Holmes makes a smart pass to Victoria Vivians who hits an easy triple and now has 24 points so far in the game.
videos.headline: Vivians' 3 gives Mississippi State the lead

videos.description: Jazzmun Holmes connects with Blair Schaefer for consecutive 3-pointers in the fourth quarter and fans get extra loud in excitement.
videos.headline: Schaefers' back-to-back 3s thrills crowd

videos.description: With less than four minutes left in the game, Jazzmun Holmes intercepts the ball from A'ja Wilson then goes coast-to-coast for a layup and draws the foul on the way up.
videos.headline: Holmes steals and creates 3-point play for Mississippi State

videos.description: Mississippi State head coach Vic Schaefer acknowledges fans after the Bulldogs defeat the Gamecocks 67-53 on Monday night.
videos.headline: Schaefer thanks sold-out crowd
